<paragraph blockId="16.[460,804,1453,1477]" box="[460,804,1453,1477]" pageId="16" pageNumber="3244">
<heading box="[460,804,1453,1477]" centered="true" fontSize="10" level="2" pageId="16" pageNumber="3244" reason="3">
<taxonomicName authority="Sowerby, 1871" authorityName="Sowerby" authorityYear="1871" box="[460,804,1453,1477]" class="Bivalvia" family="Ostreidae" genus="Ostrea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ostreida" pageId="16" pageNumber="3244" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="hanleyi">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[460,624,1453,1477]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="3244">Ostrea hanleyi</emphasis>
Sowerby, 1871
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[154,1111,1517,1733]" pageId="16" pageNumber="3244">
<emphasis box="[194,288,1517,1541]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="3244">Habitat.</emphasis>
Cemented to the undersides of limestone rocks and dead coral blocks lying on silty sand from the mid-littoral to a few metres.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="17" lastPageNumber="3245" pageId="16" pageNumber="3244" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="16.[154,1111,1517,1733]" pageId="16" pageNumber="3244">
<emphasis box="[194,335,1581,1605]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="3244">Distribution.</emphasis>
Throughout the lagoon but common in turbid areas such as at Pointe Palmiste.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[154,1111,1517,1733]" pageId="16" pageNumber="3244">
<emphasis box="[194,301,1645,1669]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="3244">Remarks.</emphasis>
This is a thin-shelled oyster, generally lacking marginal plications and of a uniform pale brown colour. It is possibly the same species as listed under 
<emphasis box="[231,365,1709,1733]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="3244">O. subucula</emphasis>
, Jousseaume by 
<bibRefCitation author="OLIVER, P. G." box="[566,712,1708,1732]" pageId="16" pageNumber="3244" refId="ref14130" refString="OLIVER, P. G., 1992, Bivalved Seashells of the Red Sea (Wiesbaden, Germany: Verlag Christa Hemmen), 330 pp." type="book" year="1992">Oliver (1992</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="OLIVER, P. G." box="[727,785,1708,1732]" pageId="16" pageNumber="3244" pagination="194 - 281" refId="ref14158" refString="OLIVER, P. G., 1995, Bivalves, in S. P. Dance (ed.) Seashells of Eastern Arabia (Dubai: Motivate), pp. 194 - 281." type="book chapter" year="1995">1995</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[159,1115,173,263]" pageId="17" pageNumber="3245">
<emphasis box="[199,278,174,198]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="3245">Range.</emphasis>
It has been found by the senior author in the Red Sea, Arabian Sea, 
<collectingCountry box="[159,273,205,229]" name="Seychelles" pageId="17" pageNumber="3245">Seychelles</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[337,454,205,229]" name="Mauritius" pageId="17" pageNumber="3245">Mauritius</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[159,1115,173,263]" box="[199,817,239,263]" pageId="17" pageNumber="3245">
